The paper proposes a new approach for optimizing neural network structures, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The use of functional steepest descent and the focus on lightweight architectures suggest that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category. The paper also mentions applications in computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and control systems (cs.SY), which are all relevant to the topic. Finally, the use of optimization techniques and neural networks suggests that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible category.
